# Epic Bot Environment Variables
#
# Where to get your credentials:
#
# 1. SLACK TOKENS (https://api.slack.com/apps)
#    - Create a new app or select existing app
#    - SLACK_BOT_TOKEN: "OAuth & Permissions" → Bot User OAuth Token (starts with xoxb-)
#    - SLACK_SIGNING_SECRET: "Basic Information" → Signing Secret
#
# 2. ANTHROPIC API KEY (https://console.anthropic.com/)
#    - Login/create account at console.anthropic.com
#    - Go to "API Keys" section
#    - Create a new key (starts with sk-ant-)
#
# 3. GITHUB TOKEN (https://github.com/settings/tokens)
#    - Go to Settings → Developer settings → Personal access tokens → Tokens (classic)
#    - Generate new token with 'repo' scope (starts with ghp_)
#    - GITHUB_OWNER: Your GitHub username or organization name
#    - GITHUB_REPO: The repository name where issues will be created

# Slack (create app at https://api.slack.com/apps)
SLACK_BOT_TOKEN=xoxb-your-token-here
SLACK_SIGNING_SECRET=your-signing-secret-here

# Port for HTTP server (Render.com sets this automatically)
# PORT=3000

# Anthropic (get key at https://console.anthropic.com/)
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-your-key-here

# GitHub (create token at https://github.com/settings/tokens)
GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_your-token-here
GITHUB_OWNER=your-github-username-or-org
GITHUB_REPO=your-repo-name
